[00:00.00]
[00:46.50]They say, "I had no choice,"
[00:53.50]but I know that isn’t true,
[00:59.50]Even standing in the dark
[01:05.50]is something we all choose.
[01:13.00]Bread upon the table,
[01:20.50]hunger in my chest,
[01:26.50]I eat not out of force,
[01:33.50]but knowing what comes next.
[01:40.00]I always had a choice,
[01:43.50]even when it hurt,
[01:46.50]Even when my heart chased fire,
[01:50.00]knowing I’d get burned.
[01:53.00]It’s not the lack of options,
[01:56.50]it’s the price we try to avoid,
[01:59.50]Every path asks something—
[02:03.00]yes, I always had a choice.
[02:18.50]Happiness isn’t waiting,
[02:24.50]it’s built with honest pain,
[02:30.50]It’s choosing to keep walking
[02:34.50]in the wind and in the rain.
[02:43.50]So don’t say you were powerless,
[02:46.50]don’t silence your own voice,
[02:50.00]Life is shaped by moments where we choose…
[02:56.50]You always had a choice.
[03:26.00]I always had a choice.
[03:32.00]